The EU has agreed to ban nearly 90% of Russian oil over the next six months as part of sanctions against Russia. How will this impact energy supply and demand in the European and global market? Less than two months after Shenzhou-13 crew members returned to earth, China's next crewed mission is on standby to launch on Sunday. What are the goals of the new mission? Are we close to completing China’s space station? To answer these questions and more, we've invited Victor Gao Zhikai, chair professor at Soochow University;Mark Sleboda, a Moscow-based international affairs & security analyst; Rick Dunham, former White House correspondent for Business Week; Zhang Fan, associateprofessor of astronomy from Beijing Normal University; and Prof. Bernard Foing, CEO of Euromoonmars Earth Space Innovation.